data.meta_description: Oct 14, 2015 - Inge Morath (1923-2002) was born in Graz, Austria. After studying languages in Berlin, she became a translator, then a journalist and the Austrian editor for Heute, an Information Service Branch publication based in Munich. All her life Morath would remain a prolific diarist and letter-writer, retaining a dual gift for words and pictures that made her unusual among her colleagues. See more ideas about inge morath, magnum photos, top photographers.
